quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  10,104,"Say: ´Mankind! if you are in any doubt about my deen, I do not worship those you worship besides Allah. Rather I worship Allah who will take you back to Him and I am commanded to be one of the muminun"
  10,105,"Turn your face towards the deen in pure natural faith, and on no account be among the idolaters"
  10,106,"Do not call on something besides Allah which can neither help nor harm you. If you do, you will then be wrongdoers.´"
  10,107,"If Allah afflicts you with harm, no one can remove it except Him. If He desires good for you, no one can avert His favour. He bestows it on whichever of His slaves He wills. He is Ever-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  10,108,"Say: ´Mankind! the truth has come to you from your Lord. Whoever is guided is only guided for his own good. Whoever is misguided is only misguided to his detriment. I have not been set over you as a guardian.´"
  10,109,Follow what has been revealed to you and be steadfast until Allah´s judgement comes. He is the Best of Judges